IMPORTANT: Specific syntax for version 0.2!

1. SHOW – display
show "text"           # text in double quotes
show 'variable/array' # content of variable or array

2. INT – integers
int 42 "name"         # NOTE: name in DOUBLE QUOTES!

3. ARRAY – arrays
array 1,2,3 "name"    # NOTE: name in DOUBLE QUOTES!

4. MATH OPERATIONS
3+2="result"          # NOTE: variable name in DOUBLE QUOTES!

5. IF / ELSE
if int "x" = 3 show 'x' else show "other"
# NOTE: variable name in DOUBLE QUOTES, display in SINGLE QUOTES

6. REDO – repetition
redo 5 show "repeat 5 times"

7. ARRAYS
leng "array"         # NOTE: name in DOUBLE QUOTES!
push "array" 99      # NOTE: name in DOUBLE QUOTES!
pop "array"          # NOTE: name in DOUBLE QUOTES!

8. FUNCTIONS
func "name"           # function name in DOUBLE QUOTES
  # function body
done
call "name"           # function name in DOUBLE QUOTES

9. INPUT
input "Text:" = 'variable'  # NOTE: variable in SINGLE QUOTES!

10. PROGRAM END
END

11. COMMENTS
# This is a comment

KEY DIFFERENCE:
- All variable/array/function names use DOUBLE QUOTES!
- Only SHOW and INPUT use single quotes for variable names!
